20"></td><td><a id="item-1" name="item-1"></a><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td valign="top"><img src="http://pelorous.totallyplc.com/media_manager/public/138/newsletter/bullet.gif" /></td><td width="10"></td><td valign="top"><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td><a href="http://www.pila.ie/bulletin/july-2012/11-july-2012/calls-for-revision-of-the-legislation-setting-up-the-ihrec-and-of-the-constitutional-convention/" style="text-decoration:none"><font face="arial" color="#E57B09">Calls for revision of the legislation & rules setting up the IHREC and of the Constitutional Convention</font></a></td></tr><tr><td height="5"></td></tr><tr><td><font face="arial">The Irish Human Rights Commission has called for the legislation setting up the new merged human rights &amp; equality body to be revised to meet UN standards, and the Irish Council for Civil Liberties has &nbsp;called on the government to hear civil society's views when reforming the Irish Constitution.</font></td></tr><tr><td height="5"></td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://www.pila.ie/bulletin/july-2012/11-july-2012/calls-for-revision-of-the-legislation-setting-up-the-ihrec-and-of-the-constitutional-convention/" style="font-size: 11px; text-decoration:none"><font face="arial" color="#E57B09">READ MORE &#8594;</font></a></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td height="15"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td width="20"></td><td><a id="item-2" name="item-2"></a><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td valign="top"><img src="http://pelorous.totallyplc.com/media_manager/public/138/newsletter/bullet.gif" /></td><td width="10"></td><td valign="top"><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td><a href="http://www.pila.ie/bulletin/july-2012/11-july-2012/involuntary-detention-of-psychiatric-patient-not-invalidated-by-lack-of-full-physical-examination/" style="text-decoration:none"><font face="arial" color="#E57B09">Involuntary detention of psychiatric patient not invalidated by lack of full physical examination</font></a></td></tr><tr><td height="5"></td></tr><tr><td><font face="arial">Section 10 of the Mental Health Act 2001 was considered, which requires a medical practitioner to promptly examine a person who is being involuntarily detained.</font></td></tr><tr><td height="5"></td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://www.pila.ie/bulletin/july-2012/11-july-2012/involuntary-detention-of-psychiatric-patient-not-invalidated-by-lack-of-full-physical-examination/" style="font-size: 11px; text-decoration:none"><font face="arial" color="#E57B09">READ MORE &#8594;</font></a></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td height="15"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td width="20"></td><td><a id="item-3" name="item-3"></a><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td valign="top"><img src="http://pelorous.totallyplc.com/media_manager/public/138/newsletter/bullet.gif" /></td><td width="10"></td><td valign="top"><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td><a href="http://www.pila.ie/bulletin/july-2012/11-july-2012/ireland-ratifies-environmental-convention-that-provides-support-for-public-interest-litigation/" style="text-decoration:none"><font face="arial" color="#E57B09">Ireland Ratifies Environmental Convention that provides support for public interest litigation</font></a></td></tr><tr><td height="5"></td></tr><tr><td><font face="arial">Minister announced Ireland's ratification of the Aarhus Convention at the Rio +20 sustainable development summit.&nbsp;</font></td></tr><tr><td height="5"></td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://www.pila.ie/bulletin/july-2012/11-july-2012/ireland-ratifies-environmental-convention-that-provides-support-for-public-interest-litigation/" style="font-size: 11px; text-decoration:none"><font face="arial" color="#E57B09">READ MORE &#8594;</font></a></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td height="15"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td width="20"></td><td><a id="item-4" name="item-4"></a><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td valign="top"><img src="http://pelorous.totallyplc.com/media_manager/public/138/newsletter/bullet.gif" /></td><td width="10"></td><td valign="top"><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td><a href="http://www.pila.ie/bulletin/july-2012/11-july-2012/body-searching-of-prisoners-in-northern-ireland-uk-prisoner-votes-and-irish-prison-standards/" style="text-decoration:none"><font face="arial" color="#E57B09">Body-searching of prisoners in Northern Ireland, UK prisoner votes and Irish prison standards.</font></a></td></tr><tr><td height="5"></td></tr><tr><td><font face="arial">Northern Ireland Court of Appeal says inflexible prisoner body-searching policy would be unlawful; Nick Clegg says that proposed House of Lords reform bill would be incompatible with UK Human Rights Act &amp; Irish Times opinion piece from criminology professor calls for a safer &amp; more human Irish prison system.&nbsp;</font></td></tr><tr><td height="5"></td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://www.pila.ie/bulletin/july-2012/11-july-2012/body-searching-of-prisoners-in-northern-ireland-uk-prisoner-votes-and-irish-prison-standards/" style="font-size: 11px; text-decoration:none"><font face="arial" color="#E57B09">READ MORE &#8594;</font></a></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td height="15"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td width="20"></td><td><a id="item-5" name="item-5"></a><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td valign="top"><img src="http://pelorous.totallyplc.com/media_manager/public/138/newsletter/bullet.gif" /></td><td width="10"></td><td valign="top"><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td><a href="http://www.pila.ie/bulletin/july-2012/11-july-2012/extradition-of-parents-the-interests-of-children-under-article-8-echr-3-uk-decisions/" style="text-decoration:none"><font face="arial" color="#E57B09">Extradition of parents & the interests of children under Article 8 ECHR - 3 UK decisions</font></a></td></tr><tr><td height="5"></td></tr><tr><td><font face="arial">The level of interference by parental extradition with Arti